The paper deals with the performance of machine learning models in predicting stochastic processes generated by probabilistic deterministic finite-state automata (PDFA). This falls under the broad category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG. The paper also discusses the performance of recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which are a popular type of neural network used for sequence modeling and prediction. This makes cs.AI and cs.NE likely sub-categories as well. The paper also touches upon the concept of causal states and predictive state representations, which are related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.SY and cs.IT possible sub-categories.
